Operating Principles (4원칙)
----------------------------

The "운영 원칙 (Operating Principles)" section in the orchestrator instruction
file (CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md) reproduces, verbatim, the behavioral guidelines
from:

  - Source:  https://github.com/multica-ai/andrej-karpathy-skills (CLAUDE.md)
  - Author:  forrestchang (multica-ai)
  - License: MIT — declared in the repository README ("License: MIT") and in
    `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` (`"license": "MIT"`). The repository contains
    no standalone LICENSE file (verified 2026-06-10).
  - The guidelines are themselves derived from Andrej Karpathy's observations
    on LLM coding pitfalls: https://x.com/karpathy/status/2015883857489522876

Modifications in this project (marked as "adapted"):

  - Layered application for the orchestrator/worker split: the full four
    principles bind the orchestrator session only.
  - The fixed "Worker 행동 규약" block in `_templates/worker-brief.md` is a
    derived translation for one-shot/headless workers: principles ② and ③
    as-is; principle ① translated to assumption-surfacing (workers have no
    user-question channel — assumptions and mismatches are surfaced in
    result.md Issues/Caveats); principle ④ is orchestrator-only.

